<h2><a name="size" id="size">size</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Syntax:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;set&gt;</span>
    size_type size<span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="br0">&#41;</span> <span class="kw4">const</span>;</pre>
<p>
The size() function returns the number of elements in the current set.
</p>

<p>
For example, the following code uses size() to determine the number of elements in a set:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">     <span class="co1">// Create a set of characters</span>
     set<span class="sy0">&lt;</span>char<span class="sy0">&gt;</span> charSet;
     <span class="kw4">const</span> <span class="kw4">char</span><span class="sy0">*</span> s <span class="sy0">=</span> <span class="st0">&quot;Hello There&quot;</span>;
     <span class="kw1">for</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">int</span> i<span class="sy0">=</span><span class="nu19">0</span>; i <span class="sy0">&lt;</span> strlen<span class="br0">&#40;</span>s<span class="br0">&#41;</span>; i<span class="sy0">++</span> <span class="br0">&#41;</span> <span class="br0">&#123;</span>
       charSet.<span class="me1">insert</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> s<span class="br0">&#91;</span>i<span class="br0">&#93;</span> <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
     <span class="br0">&#125;</span>
     <span class="co1">// Display the size of the set</span>
     <a href="http://www.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/009695399/functions/cout.html"><span class="kw3">cout</span></a> <span class="sy0">&lt;&lt;</span> charSet.<span class="me1">size</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
     <span class="co1">// output is &quot;8&quot; (the characters in the set are &quot; HTehlor&quot;)</span></pre>
<p>
